==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''aphros'', (sea foam) + ''-ite'', (Greek ending denoting a person associated with a place, etc.)

===Proper noun===
'''Aphrodite'''

# ''(Greek mythology)'': The [[goddess]] of [[beauty]] and [[love]], born when [[Cronus]] [[castrated]] [[Uranus]] and threw his [[genitalia]] into the sea

